# MVP 1 — Product & Auth Model

## Deployment model (MVP 1)

| Aspect | MVP 1 (now) | Future (SaaS) |
|--------|-------------|---------------|
| Sales | **Beli putus** — satu bisnis, satu install/deployment | Multi-tenant subscription |
| Tenancy | Single organization per instance | Workspace / org per customer |
| Public signup | **Tidak ada** | Register + plan picker |
| New team members | **Owner invite** via email → set password | Self-serve + billing seats |

**Do not build** public `/register`, open signup, or multi-tenant billing in MVP 1 unless user explicitly asks for SaaS phase.

## Auth & onboarding (MVP 1)

1. **Login only** — email + password (Supabase Auth when configured).
2. **First owner** — seeded at deploy (`hartono@chatcrm.demo` or setup script); bukan self-register.
3. **CS / Supervisor / Owner tambahan** — hanya **Owner** yang mengundang:
   - Settings → Manajemen Agent → **Undang via email**
   - Supabase `inviteUserByEmail` → email link → halaman set password (`/accept-invite`)
   - Trigger DB link `auth.users` ke baris `agents` via `user_metadata.agent_id`
4. **Forgot password** — tetap ada untuk semua role.
5. **Demo shortcuts** di login — hanya dev/demo; label jujur.

## Role rules (unchanged)

- `cs` — assigned customers + manual shares
- `supervisor` — team view, manage agents (role change), no invite
- `owner` — supervisor + **invite users**, billing, export approval, field rules

Invite permission: **`role === 'owner'` only** — not `manage_agents` alone.

## Copy (Indonesian)

- Login footer: *"Belum punya akun? Hubungi owner bisnis Anda."* — **not** "Daftar sekarang"
- Invite success: *"Undangan dikirim ke {email}"*
- Accept invite page: *"Atur password untuk akun ChatCRM Anda"*

## Technical constraints

- Invite **must** use server function + `SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY` (admin API) — never expose secret in client.
- No `signUp` / public registration in app code.
- DB trigger `handle_new_user`: link via `agent_id` metadata only — **do not** auto-create agent on orphan signup.
- Agent row created **before** invite (status `pending`); becomes `active` after user sets password.

## When implementing SaaS later

- Add `organizations`, `memberships`, subdomain routing
- Replace single-tenant seed with org provisioning
- Re-enable guarded registration or checkout → provision flow
- See future note in `AGENTS.md` — do not half-implement SaaS in MVP 1 files
